(983,	173,	'excerpt',	'<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once upon a midnight dreary, while I pondered, weak and weary,</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Over many a quaint and curious volume of forgotten lore,</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While I nodded, nearly napping, suddenly there came a tapping,</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As of some one gently rapping, rapping at my chamber door.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\"\'T is some visiter,\" I muttered, \"tapping at my chamber door</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Only this, and nothing more.\"</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
