(50,	1,	'2023-07-18 03:37:15',	'2023-07-18 03:37:15',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In 1688, Mary Collier was born to a poor family in West Sussex, England. She worked various low-paying jobs, including as a washer and as a brewer, and entertained herself by writing poetry. Eventually, with enough encouragement, she began to publish her poems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Mary Collier',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'mary-collier',	'',	'',	'2023-07-18 03:37:15',	'2023-07-18 03:37:15',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=50',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
(51,	1,	'2023-07-18 03:41:35',	'2023-07-18 03:41:35',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Anne Bronte was born on January 17, 1820, in England. Her mother died before she turned two. Just a few years later, her two eldest sisters died of tuberculosis while at boarding school.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As children, Emily and her siblings, Charlotte, Anne, and Branwell, began writing poems and stories. The three sisters published a book of poetry together in adulthood. They chose to use male pen names to avoid the widespread prejudice female authors faced at the time. Anne\'s pseudonym was Acton Bell. She also published her novels <em>Agnes Grey </em>and <em>The Tenant of Wildfell Hall</em>. The sisters eventually revealed their true identities and became celebrated for their work.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Anne lost her brother, Branwell, and her sister, Emily, in 1848. That same winter, Anne caught a flu which led to her death on May 28, 1849. She was 29 years old. During her short life, she became one of the earliest feminist authors, and her work is treasured to this day.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Anne Bronte',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'anne-bronte',	'',	'',	'2023-07-18 03:41:35',	'2023-07-18 03:41:35',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=51',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
