(53,	1,	'2023-07-18 03:45:38',	'2023-07-18 03:45:38',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Emily Bronte was born on July 30, 1818, in England. Her mother died when she was only three years old. A few years later, her two eldest sisters died of tuberculosis while at boarding school.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Possibly as a way of coping with these tragedies, Emily and her siblings, Charlotte, Anne, and Branwell, began writing poems and stories. In adulthood, the three sisters published a book of poetry together, using male pen names to avoid the widespread prejudice female authors faced at the time. Emily\'s pseudonym was Ellis Bell, and she also used this name when she wrote her brilliant novel, <em>Wuthering Heights</em>. The sisters eventually revealed their true identities and became celebrated for their work.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Emily\'s brother, Branwell, passed away in 1848. While attending his funeral, Emily caught a cold, which developed into tuberculosis. She died from this disease on December 19, 1848. To this day, she is remembered as a literary genius.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Emily Bronte',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'emily-bronte',	'',	'',	'2023-07-18 03:45:38',	'2023-07-18 03:45:38',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=53',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
