(55,	1,	'2023-07-18 03:51:30',	'2023-07-18 03:51:30',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Charlotte Bronte was born on April 21, 1816, in England. Her mother died when she was only five years old, and when she was nine her two eldest sisters died of tuberculosis while at boarding school.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Possibly as a way of coping with these tragedies, Charlotte and her siblings, Emily, Anne, and Branwell, began writing poems and stories. In adulthood, the three sisters published a book of poetry together. They chose to use male pen names to avoid the widespread prejudice female authors faced at the time. Charlotte\'s pseudonym was Currer Bell, and she also used this name when she wrote her highly acclaimed debut novel, <em>Jane Eyre</em>. The sisters eventually revealed their true identities and became celebrated for their work.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Jane lost all three of her siblings to illnesses in 1848 and 1849. A few years later, she began to fall in love with a clergymen who worked with her father, a man named Arthur Bell Nichols. The two married in 1854 and soon conceived a child, however, Jane died while pregnant in 1855. Today she is remembered not only for <em>Jane Eyre </em>and her poetry, but also two other novels, <em>Villette </em>and <em>The Professor</em>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Charlotte Bronte',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'charlotte-bronte',	'',	'',	'2023-07-18 03:51:30',	'2023-07-18 03:51:30',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=55',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
