(57,	1,	'2023-07-18 03:56:31',	'2023-07-18 03:56:31',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Percy Bysshe Shelley was born on August 4, 1792, to a wealthy English family. Despite his privileged background, Shelley adopted radical politics early on and expressed a desire to redistribute his familys money to the less fortunate. He wrote political essays, but he became most well known as a poet.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Though he drowned at only 29 years of age, Shelley left behind many poems that have been admired throughout generations. He had six children, including four with his second wife, renowned novelist Mary Wollstonecraft Shelley.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Percy Shelley',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'percy-shelley',	'',	'',	'2023-07-18 03:56:31',	'2023-07-18 03:56:31',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=57',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
