(59,	1,	'2023-07-18 04:02:39',	'2023-07-18 04:02:39',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mary Wollstonecraft Godwin was born in England on August 30, 1797, to philosophers William Godwin and Mary Wollstonecraft. Tragically, Mary Wollstonecraft died shortly after her daughters birth. Young Mary Godwin grew up feeling mistreated by her step mother and cherishing the feminist novels and nonfiction books written by the mother she never got to know.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By young adulthood, Mary had herself become an incredible author. Her groundbreaking science fiction novel, <em>Frankenstein; or, the Modern Prometheus </em>was published when she was only twenty years old. She went on to write several more novels, as well as short stories and nonfiction works. She also helped promote the poetry of her husband, Percy Bysshe Shelley.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Throughout the years, tragedy continued to plague Mary Shelleys life. Three of her four children died in infancy. Her husband drowned when he was 29. Mary herself died from a brain tumor at only 53. Today she is remembered around the world as the mother of the science fiction genre.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Mary Wollstonecraft Shelley',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'mary-wollstonecraft-shelley',	'',	'',	'2023-07-18 04:02:39',	'2023-07-18 04:02:39',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=59',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
