(61,	1,	'2023-07-18 04:06:57',	'2023-07-18 04:06:57',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Charles Lutwidge Dodgson was born on January 27, 1832, and later adopted the pen name Lewis Carroll. His most successful works were the literary nonsense novels <em>Alices Adventures in Wonderland </em>and its sequel, <em>Through the Looking Glass. </em>Dodgson was also a poet, teacher, and mathematician.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Lewis Carroll',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'lewis-carroll',	'',	'',	'2023-07-18 04:06:57',	'2023-07-18 04:06:57',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=61',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
