(63,	1,	'2023-07-18 04:11:01',	'2023-07-18 04:11:01',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Jules Verne was born to a well-off family on February 8, 1828 in Nantes, France. He became known for writing poems, plays, and novels. His sci-fi adventure novels, in particular, remain widely beloved to this day. Verne also wrote nonfiction works about science, literature, and his own life. He died after a long illness at the age of 77, leaving a wife, a son, and two step-daughters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Jules Verne',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'jules-verne',	'',	'',	'2023-07-18 04:11:01',	'2023-07-18 04:11:01',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=63',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
