(65,	1,	'2023-07-18 04:15:55',	'2023-07-18 04:15:55',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Oscar Wilde was born in Ireland on October 16, 1854. His father was a renowned surgeon and his mother was a poet and Irish nationalist. Oscar himself became a celebrated poet, playwright, and author. Though he married a woman, Constance Lloyd, and had two sons, Wilde also participated in same-sex relationships throughout his life. Tragically, he was arrested and imprisoned for homosexuality. The brutal treatment he endured in prison contributed to his death at only 46 years old.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Oscar Wilde',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'oscar-wilde',	'',	'',	'2023-07-18 04:15:55',	'2023-07-18 04:15:55',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=65',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
