(74,	1,	'2023-07-18 23:28:42',	'2023-07-18 23:28:42',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Agatha was born to a wealthy English family on September 15, 1890, but chose to become a working woman. Throughout her adult life, she served in military pharmacies (where she became an expert on various poisons) and assisted her archaeologist husband on excavations in the Middle East. She also found time to write eighty books, which have since sold over two billion copies combined, cementing her place as one of the worlds most beloved authors to this day.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Agatha Christie',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'agatha-christie',	'',	'',	'2023-07-18 23:28:42',	'2023-07-18 23:28:42',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=74',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
