(78,	1,	'2023-07-19 15:58:55',	'2023-07-19 15:58:55',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On September 21, 1866, in Kent, England, Herbert George Wells was born into a working class family. After a couple of unsuccessful apprenticeships and years bouncing between schools, he began earning money by writing articles. He then transitioned to writing stories, novels, and nonfiction pieces. By the time of his death at age 79, he had written over fifty novels, including several that shaped new subgenres of science fiction. Wells is also remembered as a father of four and an outspoken socialist.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'H. G. Wells',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'h-g-wells',	'',	'',	'2023-07-19 15:58:55',	'2023-07-19 15:58:55',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=78',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
