(82,	1,	'2023-07-19 17:45:08',	'2023-07-19 17:45:08',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Born in West Africa around the year 1753, the young girl who would become known as Phillis Wheatley was kidnapped at about seven years old. She was forced onto a slave ship called <em>The Phillis </em>and brought to Boston. There, the family who bought her from her captors named her after the ship and themselves.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Two of the Wheatleys children taught Phillis to read and write, and the family soon noticed her incredible talent for writing poetry. Though forced to write what her masters and other white patrons wanted to read, Phillis Wheatley managed to get a volume of her poetry published. In doing so, she helped pave the way for future generations of Black authors in America.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Phillis Wheatley',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'phillis-wheatley',	'',	'',	'2023-07-19 17:45:08',	'2023-07-19 17:45:08',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=82',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
