(88,	1,	'2023-07-19 18:23:38',	'2023-07-19 18:23:38',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Born November 16, 1836, David Laamea Kamananakapu Mahinulani Naloiaehuokalani Lumialani Kalakaua was the last king and second-last monarch of the Kingdom of Hawaii. He came to the throne on February 12, 1874 and ruled until his death on January 20, 1891. Known as the Merrie Monarch, King Kalakaua loved to celebrate traditional Hawaiian culture and played a role in revitalizing Hula dancing, surfing, and the Hawaiian martial art known as Lua. He married a woman named Kapiolani but the couple had no biological children. Before his death, King Kalakaua named his sister, Liliuokalani, to be his successor to the throne.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'David Kalakaua',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'david-kalakaua',	'',	'',	'2023-07-19 18:23:38',	'2023-07-19 18:23:38',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=88',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
