(99,	1,	'2023-07-19 18:50:02',	'2023-07-19 18:50:02',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Frederick Douglass eventually chose to celebrate Valentines Day as his birthday. Born into slavery, he wasnt allowed to know his true date of birth, just that it was sometime around the year 1818. He also was barely allowed to know his mother at all before she died when he was only about seven years old. But all his life he knew the cruelties of slavery. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Young Frederick knew that slave owners didnt want slaves to be able to read. For this reason, he taught himself to read and write and paid close attention to everything that was happening around him. These skills helped him escape, and once he did, they allowed him to become a powerful voice for abolition. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a free man, Douglass became an author, publisher, preacher, statesman, husband and father.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Frederick Douglass',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'frederick-douglass',	'',	'',	'2023-07-19 18:50:02',	'2023-07-19 18:50:02',	'',	0,	'http://the-book-marketplace.local/?post_type=author-profile&#038;p=99',	0,	'author-profile',	'',	0),
